{
  "doc_id": "46183",
  "text": "Although few in number, all studies have reported high blood lead levels in Pakistan since 1989 [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] . Comparatively higher blood lead levels were reported from the megacity Karachi (range 7.2-38.2 µg/dL) and Islamabad with less dense traffic (3.22-2.3 µg/dL) [CITATION_8] [CITATION_9] [CITATION_10] [CITATION_11] [CITATION_12] [CITATION_13] [CITATION_14] . Moreover, higher blood lead levels have also been reported among children of industrial workers [CITATION_15] .",
